@startuml
scale 1600 width
title VBoxManage clipboard serve - overview state machine
hide empty description
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam dpi 96

legend right
  serve subscribes to:
  SourceChanged, FormatChanged, DataChanged,
  DataRequested, Transfer, Error and ModeChanged.

  VBoxManage is only the policy/event-loop client.
  Native host clipboard access stays in Main.

  Focused companion diagrams split out the
  Source/Format, Host-to-Guest, Guest-to-Host,
  lazy Host Data Request and file Transfer paths.
endlegend

[*] --> Setup : VBoxManage clipboard <vm> serve
Setup : Get IClipboard
Setup : Get IClipboard::hostClipboard
Setup : Register IClipboard::eventSource listener
Setup : Install signal handler
Setup --> ServeLoop : ready
Setup --> Failed : COM error or no host endpoint

state ServeLoop {
  [*] --> Waiting

  Waiting : Wait for next event
  Waiting : or timeout / signal
  Waiting --> Stopping : timeout or signal
  Waiting --> Dispatch : event received

  Dispatch : Decode VBoxEventType
  Dispatch --> GuestFormats : SourceChanged/FormatChanged\nsource == Guest
  Dispatch --> HostToGuestData : DataChanged\nsource == Host
  Dispatch --> GuestToHostData : DataChanged\nsource == Guest
  Dispatch --> HostDataRequest : DataRequested\nrequest == Copy/Guest
  Dispatch --> TransferEvent : Transfer
  Dispatch --> FailedEvent : Error
  Dispatch --> Continue : ModeChanged, ignored source,\nunsupported or empty data

  GuestFormats : Filter supported MIME formats
  GuestFormats : Suppress self-induced echo
  GuestFormats : IHostClipboard::ReportFormats(Copy, Guest, formats)
  GuestFormats --> Continue : success or ignored
  GuestFormats --> FailedEvent : COM error

  HostToGuestData : IClipboard::WriteDataRaw(Copy, Host, mime, bytes)
  HostToGuestData : Store host-owned Main item
  HostToGuestData : Report formats to guest service
  HostToGuestData --> Continue : success
  HostToGuestData --> FailedEvent : COM error

  GuestToHostData : IHostClipboard::SetData(Copy, Guest, mime, bytes)
  GuestToHostData : Report native host format
  GuestToHostData : Write payload if backend supports it
  GuestToHostData --> Continue : success
  GuestToHostData --> FailedEvent : COM error

  HostDataRequest : IClipboard::ReadDataRaw(action, mime)
  HostDataRequest : IHostClipboard::ProvideData(requestId, Copy, Guest, mime, bytes)
  HostDataRequest --> Continue : success, ignored or warning

  TransferEvent : Inspect IClipboardTransferEvent
  TransferEvent : Use IClipboardTransferManager controls
  TransferEvent --> TransferApproval : interaction == Approval
  TransferEvent --> TransferConflict : Overwrite, Rename, Destination\nor ErrorRecovery
  TransferEvent --> TransferProgress : Added, InProgress, Completed,\nCanceled, Failed or Removed

  TransferApproval : approve() or deny(reason)
  TransferApproval --> Continue

  TransferConflict : respond(transfer, interaction, path,\nresponse, responsePath, flags)
  TransferConflict --> Continue

  TransferProgress : update UI / log state
  TransferProgress --> Continue

  Continue --> Waiting

  FailedEvent : Print serve failure
  FailedEvent --> Stopping
}

ServeLoop --> Cleanup : stopped
Failed --> Cleanup
Cleanup : IHostClipboard::Clear()
Cleanup : Unregister listener
Cleanup : Uninstall signal handler
Cleanup --> [*]

note right of GuestFormats
  Main ReportFormats:
  - validates Guest source, mode and MIME types
  - maps MIME to SHCLFORMATS
  - updates current advertised Guest formats
  - calls GuestShCl::reportFormatsToHost()
end note

note right of GuestToHostData
  Main SetData:
  - validates Guest source, mode, MIME and size
  - converts Main MIME bytes to protocol bytes
  - reports format to native backend
  - writes data when backend implements it
  - preserves generic Main clipboard cache/source
end note

note right of HostDataRequest
  Native lazy paste path:
  - backend asks Main for advertised Guest data
  - Main registers a one-shot pending request ID
  - OnClipboardDataRequested wakes serve
  - ProvideData consumes the ID and stores matching data
  - cached matching data may still be used as fallback
end note

note bottom of HostToGuestData
  Host-to-guest while serving keeps using the generic
  IClipboard path. Guest-to-host native publication uses
  IHostClipboard so guest-owned data is not reflected back
  as host-owned clipboard state.
end note

note right of TransferEvent
  File transfers are implicit. Main creates and tracks
  IClipboardTransfer objects; the serve client receives
  IClipboardTransferEvent notifications and controls
  policy through IClipboardTransferManager. There is no
  IClipboardTransferOperation wrapper.
end note

@enduml
' EOF
